    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      I'm Jonathan Malkin. Solo founder of Open Door Learning LLC, based in Austin, Texas.
    </p>

    <p>
      I spent 20+ years in enterprise technology. Presales, solutions engineering, business analysis, project management. The common thread: translating between technical and business audiences, figuring out what people actually need, and building toward it.
    </p>

    <p>
      I left that career in June 2025 to build my own thing. Now I build software, automations, and assessment tools for businesses and communities that mainstream tech ignores.
    </p>

    <h2>What I Build</h2>

    <ul>
      <li><strong><a href="/jules/">Jules</a></strong>. An open-source AI operational system that runs my business. Content pipelines, research, scheduling, reporting, code. Built on Claude Code. The system is the proof that the approach works.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/projects/">Assessment tools</a></strong>. Interactive personality assessments and self-discovery frameworks for underserved audiences. 200+ daily users on the first one. More in development.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/articles/">Articles &amp; newsletter</a></strong>. Practitioner writing on AI automation, solo founding, and building for underserved markets.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="work-with-me">Work With Me</h2>

    <p>
      I take on consulting and advisory work in three areas:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Automation architecture.</strong> Designing AI-powered operational systems, workflows, and automations for solo founders and small teams. I've built one that runs a business. I can help you build yours.</li>
      <li><strong>Technical advisory.</strong> Fractional technical leadership for non-technical founders building software products. I translate between what the business needs and what the technology can do.</li>
      <li><strong>Speaking and workshops.</strong> AI-assisted solo founding, building for underserved markets, and the practical reality of AI agents in production.</li>
    </ul>

